\"text\\\":\\\"**Evaluating class loading strategy**\\\\n\\\\nI need to find additional loads for the `BridgeClassLoaderFactoryInnerBridgeClassLoaderTest.java`. Ensuring that the class is public at the top level is important. I wonder if the methods should be in the default package, or if the test method can be package-private. I need to consider using NativeImageSupport too. If it doesn't support dynamic loading, I should catch an Error. If an exception occurs during reflection, I'm thinking through how to manage that as well. If there's an UnsupportedFeatureError, I'll need to create a file since there's no current one-to-one mapping.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_A8wFiKWysddu0RjuclAvhMlx|fc_0c5e9de1fa5872780169fc47bcf99c81a0b5b06114e745060e\", \"name\": \"write\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/org.modelmapper/modelmapper/3.2.0/src/test/java/org_modelmapper/modelmapper/BridgeClassLoaderFactoryInnerBridgeClassLoaderTest.java\", \"content\": \"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage org_modelmapper.modelmapper;\\n\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThatThrownBy;\\n\\nimport java.lang.reflect.Method;\\nimport java.util.HashMap;\\nimport java.util.Map;\\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\nimport org.modelmapper.internal.BridgeClassLoaderFactory;\\nimport org.modelmapper.internal.bytebuddy.ByteBuddy;\\nimport org.modelmapper.internal.bytebuddy.description.modifier.Visibility;\\nimport org.modelmapper.internal.bytebuddy.dynamic.DynamicType;\\n\\npublic class BridgeClassLoaderFactoryInnerBridgeClassLoaderTest {\\n    private static final String GENERATED_PACKAGE =\\n            \\\"org_modelmapper.modelmapper.bridge.generated\\\";\\n    private static final String ADDITIONAL_INTERFACE = GENERATED_PACKAGE + \\\".AdditionalContract\\\";\\n    private static final String ADDITIONAL_ONLY = GENERATED_PACKAGE + \\\".AdditionalOnly\\\";\\n    private static final String SOURCE_TYPE = GENERATED_PACKAGE + \\\".SourceType\\\";\\n    private static final String CGLIB_INTERNAL_TYPE =\\n            \\\"org.modelmapper.internal.cglib.proxy.Enhancer\\\";\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void delegatesInternalAndHierarchyTypesFromBridgeClassLoaderFindClass() throws Exception {\\n        try {\\n            BridgeScenario.run();\\n        } catch (Error error) {\\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\\n                throw error;\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    private static final class BridgeScenario {\\n        private static void run() throws Exception {\\n            Map<String, byte[]> additionalDefinitions = new HashMap<>();\\n            additionalDefinitions.put(ADDITIONAL_INTERFACE, makeInterface(ADDITIONAL_INTERFACE));\\n            additionalDefinitions.put(ADDITIONAL_ONLY, makeClass(ADDITIONAL_ONLY));\\n            DefiningClassLoader additionalClassLoader = new DefiningClassLoader(\\n                    BridgeClassLoaderFactoryInnerBridgeClassLoaderTest.class.getClassLoader(),\\n                    additionalDefinitions);\\n            Class<?> additionalInterface = additionalClassLoader.loadClass(ADDITIONAL_INTERFACE);\\n\\n            Map<String, byte[]> sourceDefinitions = new HashMap<>();\\n            sourceDefinitions.put(SOURCE_TYPE, makeSourceClass(additionalInterface));\\n            SourceClassLoader sourceClassLoader = new SourceClassLoader(\\n                    BridgeClassLoaderFactoryInnerBridgeClassLoaderTest.class.getClassLoader(),\\n                    sourceDefinitions,\\n                    additionalInterface);\\n            Class<?> sourceType = sourceClassLoader.loadClass(SOURCE_TYPE);\\n\\n            ClassLoader bridgeClassLoader = bridgeClassLoaderFor(sourceType);\\n            assertThat(bridgeClassLoader.getClass().getName())\\n                    .endsWith(\\\"BridgeClassLoaderFactory$BridgeClassLoader\\\");\\n\\n            assertThatThrownBy(() -> bridgeClassLoader.loadClass(CGLIB_INTERNAL_TYPE))\\n                    .isInstanceOf(ClassNotFoundException.class);\\n\\n            Class<?> loadedAdditionalType = bridgeClassLoader.loadClass(ADDITIONAL_ONLY);\\n            assertThat(loadedAdditionalType.getName()).isEqualTo(ADDITIONAL_ONLY);\\n            assertThat(loadedAdditionalType.getClassLoader()).isSameAs(additionalClassLoader);\\n        }\\n\\n        private static byte[] makeInterface(String name) {\\n            DynamicType.Unloaded<?> unloaded = new ByteBuddy()\\n                    .makeInterface()\\n                    .modifiers(Visibility.PUBLIC)\\n                    .name(name)\\n                    .make();\\n            return unloaded.getBytes();\\n        }\\n\\n        private static byte[] makeClass(String name) {\\n            DynamicType.Unloaded<?> unloaded = new ByteBuddy()\\n                    .subclass(Object.class)\\n                    .modifiers(Visibility.PUBLIC)\\n                    .name(name)\\n                    .make();\\n            return unloaded.getBytes();\\n        }\\n\\n        private static byte[] makeSourceClass(Class<?> additionalInterface) {\\n            DynamicType.Unloaded<?> unloaded = new ByteBuddy()\\n                    .subclass(Object.class)\\n                    .implement(additionalInterface)\\n                    .modifiers(Visibility.PUBLIC)\\n                    .name(SOURCE_TYPE)\\n                    .make();\\n            return unloaded.getBytes();\\n        }\\n\\n        private static ClassLoader bridgeClassLoaderFor(Class<?> sourceType) throws Exception {\\n            Method getClassLoader = BridgeClassLoaderFactory.class.getDeclaredMethod(\\n                    \\\"getClassLoader\\\",\\n                    Class.class);\\n            getClassLoader.setAccessible(true);\\n            return (ClassLoader) getClassLoader.invoke(null, sourceType);\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    private static class DefiningClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\\n        private final Map<String, byte[]> definitions;\\n\\n        DefiningClassLoader(ClassLoader parent, Map<String, byte[]> definitions) {\\n            super(parent);\\n            this.definitions = definitions;\\n        }\\n\\n        @Override\\n        protected Class<?> loadClass(String name, boolean resolve) throws ClassNotFoundException {\\n            synchronized (getClassLoadingLock(name)) {\\n                Class<?> loadedClass = findLoadedClass(name);\\n                if (loadedClass == null) {\\n                    byte[] classBytes = definitions.get(name);\\n                    if (classBytes == null) {\\n                        loadedClass = super.loadClass(name, false);\\n                    } else {\\n                        loadedClass = defineClass(name, classBytes, 0, classBytes.length);\\n                    }\\n                }\\n                if (resolve) {\\n                    resolveClass(loadedClass);\\n                }\\n                return loadedClass;\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    private static final class SourceClassLoader extends DefiningClassLoader {\\n        private final Class<?> additionalInterface;\\n\\n        SourceClassLoader(\\n                ClassLoader parent,\\n                Map<String, byte[]> definitions,\\n                Class<?> additionalInterface) {\\n            super(parent, definitions);\\n            this.additionalInterface = additionalInterface;\\n        }\\n\\n        @Override\\n        protected Class<?> loadClass(String name, boolean resolve) throws ClassNotFoundException {\\n            if (ADDITIONAL_INTERFACE.equals(name)) {\\n                return additionalInterface;\\n            }\\n            return super.loadClass(name, resolve);\\n    