pile. I'll investigate this further.\\n\\n**Exploring class loading and ASM**\\n\\nI think the easiest way might be to ensure that the source type's class hierarchy includes the additionalClassLoader in BridgeClassLoaderFactory. Since it retrieves appType's interfaces at runtime, the source class should implement the interface from this class loader. I can define class bytes manually using ASM to implement the ADDITIONAL_INTERFACE internal name, which avoids ByteBuddy validation. Also, the internal CGLIB class may not exist in ModelMapper 3.2. I should edit the import to remove ByteBuddy modifiers and use ASM class manipulation instead. I wonder if a class can indeed exist without a constructor.\\n\\n**Clarifying class instantiation and interface generation**\\n\\nIt seems that instantiation isn't necessary, but loading it might be acceptable? The verifier could accept it if I add a constructor. I'll generate the interface with the necessary access modifiers: ACC_PUBLIC, ACC_ABSTRACT, and ACC_INTERFACE, using version V1_8. For the source class, I need to make it ACC_PUBLIC and ACC_SUPER, ensuring that it implements the interface's internal name. I should also include a public constructor that calls Object.<init>, similar for the AdditionalOnly class.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_0c5e9de1fa5872780169fc47fec91081a084c9b9fbe7dac0a4\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp_EgJlJyhc-u9lhFVIzzljnj3GqGfH7zYiMuS_qCI_5cVn8fEmKXuuzlGQgGZVOxmIBmgbDyBvbbEKMWGl7Csl6-wn-VIFUpIl8Y-TKEPHSVM4MZTWSEv5tdSFLui7RwEAhEJCCbII_eVvyxcj1cP46Ke-V-4BfDmyLkkieEH6pPuFDUV9jGAOjndfmpwGF5jqIkyp3PionmLMrYVZj3-1cvtuUzrnzqUWIvM_NiQTUbRH9Vnc6Re_4-EDngcygaBygbJbqDo6BtnYsNV4weQ1JWxDNMT6UNlf__vgdB2Fe1D8b6cumBausy-rSvknQsPUt9xMSptedRa6qU6iRXsEZqfHqLBkZRbwMDB2XAeQWa57DmG2P36Ej0WM4XM6kVCmx2CQQQQTdQuXslNoJpf4KGl5YNZzgADcrq6B2Tv-KL4I3aDMqVN1YtxMgkyIJx_HNlMEOWe9qbUhmP4jg_Hv7gTKlVEQ9gwS_SZojkRpZeTSqOnttRfHPNS9BpQsMdXU1oT3XGmqexEcGW0PUi5VoZNqYiXXG01bKMohkrIcQImqT